headline: Stryker (SYK) Margins Fall on $1.4B Loss, Challenging Bullish Profit Recovery Narrative
summary: Stryker (SYK) reported current net profit margins of 12.1%, a step down from last year’s 16.3%, with the latest results impacted by a one-off $1.4 billion loss. Notably, earnings forecasts call for annual growth of 17.3% going forward, outpacing the broader US market’s 15.9%, even as five-year annual earnings growth landed at 14.1% and turned negative in the past year.
